snippet: Rescue workers struggled to reach dozens of people trapped in the rubble of a medicine factory that collapsed in Lahore on Monday, killing at least nine people, officials said.
abstract: Rescue workers struggle to reach dozens of people trapped in the rubble of a medicine factory that collapsed in Lahore, Pakistan, killing at least nine people; at least 32 people are still believed to be trapped.
lead_paragraph: Rescue workers struggled to reach dozens of people trapped in the rubble of a medicine factory that collapsed in Lahore on Monday, killing at least nine people, officials said.
